      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Obtain information about parameters related to processor availability, cache size, and performance-level characteristics on the system by using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/kernel/1387446-sysctlbyname",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function. These parameters provide details about your system that can aid in tuning performance. For example, you can obtain the count of the highest-performing processor cores to spawn a worker thread for each core. Or you can determine the size of the L2 cache and the number of processor cores that share it to perform software cache-blocking optimization.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "3901384",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Determine processor characteristics",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The system enables a processor core when itâ€™s powered on and available for thread scheduling. Each logical processor core executes a software thread that the operating system manages. On systems where the number of logical processor cores exceeds the number of physical processor cores, two or more logical processor cores share a physical core through simultaneous multithreading (SMT). The following parameters provide processor availability information about the system on chip (SoC):",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "definition": {
                "content": [
                  {
                    "inlineContent": [
                      {
                        "text": "The number of enabled logical processor cores in the SoC. This is an alias of ",
                        "type": "text"
                      },
                      {
                        "code": "hw.logicalcpu",
                        "type": "codeVoice"
                      },
                      {
                        "text": ".",
                        "type": "text"
                      }
                    ],
                    "type": "paragraph"
                  }
                ]
              },
              "term": {
                "inlineContent": [
